</article><article id='kontext' class='experiments single'><aside class='actions'><a class='comment' href='/experiments/kontext'>4</a></aside><h2>Kontext</h2>
<a href="http://lab.hakim.se/kontext" class="image-link" title="Open Kontext">
	<img src="http://s3.amazonaws.com/hakim-static/portfolio/images/kontext.png" alt="Kontext" width="320" height="205">
</a>
<p>
	A context-shift transition inspired by iOS. Created using JavaScript, CSS 3D transforms and CSS Animations.
</p>

<div class="launch-dock">
	<a class="launch-button" href="https://github.com/hakimel/kontext">Source on GitHub</a>
	<a class="launch-button" href="http://lab.hakim.se/kontext">Live Demo</a>
</div><footer><time datetime='2013-02-26'>2013-02-26</time><a class='footer-comment' href='/experiments/kontext'>4 comments</a></footer></article><article id='sketch-toy' class='projects double'><aside class='actions'><a class='comment' href='/projects/sketch-toy'>3</a></aside><h2>Sketch Toy</h2>
<a href="http://sketchtoy.com" class="image-link" title="Visit sketchtoy.com">
	<img src="http://d1835mevib0k1p.cloudfront.net/portfolio/images/sketchtoy.png" alt="Sketch Toy" width="695" height="320">
</a>
<div class="two-columns">
	
	<p>
		In early 2011 I released a small experiment called Sketch. It's a drawing application where lines appear to vibrate slightly 
		like in an old cartoon. Sketches can be saved to a unique link and when shared, the sketch will replay as it was originally 
		drawn.
	</p>
	<p>
		Sketch saw a good amount of interest right off the bat and I was really excited when it crossed 100,000 saved drawings. After 
		that initial rush however it quieted down quickly. Nothing unexpected there, that's the lifecycle I've come to expect from 
		releasing many different personal projects and experiments. 
	</p>
	<p>
		Fast forward to late November 2012.
	</p>
	<p>
		Out of nowhere Sketch started seeing a lot of traffic from a site that I'd never heard the name of before: <a href="http://ask.fm">ask.fm</a>. 
		According to Wikipedia <q>"ask.fm is an interest-based social Q&amp;A website"</q> though I'm still not entirely sure what that means. From 
		there it continued to spread to other sites and at the time of writing Facebook is the biggest referrer. 
	</p>
	<h3>Scaling up</h3>
	<p>
		The traffic spike ended up being much too heavy for my old host to handle and the server started breaking down during peak hours with a few
		thousand concurrent visitors. It was pretty excruciating. 
	</p>
	<p>
		I ended up migrating the project &mdash; including a 5GB MySQL databse &mdash; to a new Linux server on <a href="aws.amazon.com">AWS</a>. This 
		was challenging considering I've never set up and configured a server before but it was definitely worth it. After working through the initial  
		quirks of getting everything up and running it's been much easier to monitor and scale up further. There's also been further optimization like 
		moving all static assets to a CDN, adding a large cache layer in front of database read/writes and frequently sharding tables. 
	</p>
	<p>
		Beyond changing servers I also felt it was time for a new name since Sketch was too generic. I ended up going with Sketch Toy 
		which had the big plus of a free domain, Facebook and Twitter name: 
		<br>- <a href="http://sketchtoy.com">sketchtoy.com</a> 
		<br>- <a href="http://twitter.com/sketchtoy">twitter.com/sketchtoy</a> 
		<br>- <a href="http://facebook.com/sketchtoy">facebook.com/sketchtoy</a>
	</p>
	<h3>Challenges</h3>
	<p>
		It's been about a month since traffic first surged and it has now stabilized at 800k-1m visits per day. During peak hours that means 
		somewhere around 10-13k concurrent visitors which is very strenuous even with the new setup and probably won't scale much further. 
	</p>
	<p>
		The second challenge is storage. Sketches are saved as compressed JSON blobs but with around 400k saves per day, the databse is still 
		growing by a few GB each week. Unfortunately I believe the only real solution to this is to delete old sketches with few views.
	</p>
	<p>
		But these are fun problems to have. It's been a great opportunity to learn about server configuration and I look forward to continuing 
		to learn more as I go.
	</p>
	
</div>
<div class="launch-dock">
	<a class="launch-button" href="http://facebook.com/sketchtoy">Sketch Toy on Facebook</a>
	<a class="launch-button" href="http://sketchtoy.com">http://sketchtoy.com</a>
</div><footer><time datetime='2012-12-27'>2012-12-27</time><a class='footer-comment' href='/projects/sketch-toy'>3 comments</a></footer></article><article id='hypnos' class='experiments single'><aside class='actions'><a class='comment' href='/experiments/hypnos'>1</a></aside><h2>Hypnos</h2>
