</div><footer><time datetime='2012-10-22'>2012-10-22</time><a class='footer-comment' href='/thoughts/gdl-interview'>3 comments</a></footer></article><article id='fokus' class='experiments single'><aside class='actions'><a class='comment' href='/experiments/fokus'>13</a></aside><h2>Fokus</h2>
<a href="http://lab.hakim.se/fokus/" class="image-link" title="View demo">
	<img src="http://s3.amazonaws.com/hakim-static/portfolio/images/fokus.png" alt="Fokus" width="320" height="320">
</a>
<p>
	Fokus emphasizes anything you select by covering the rest of the page with semi-transparent black.
</p>
<p>
	This was written in JavaScript and uses a <code>&lt;canvas&gt;</code> element to paint the cover. The library has no dependencies and weighs in at around 3kb. Works in most modern browsers except IE and touch devices. If you want to use this on your site you just need to include the <a href="https://github.com/hakimel/Fokus/blob/master/js/fokus.min.js">fokus.min.js</a> script.
</p>
<p>
	Fokus is also available as a <a href="https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/flkkpmjbbpijiedjdgnhkcgopgnflehe">Chrome extension</a>.
</p>

<div class="launch-dock">
	<a class="launch-button" href="https://github.com/hakimel/fokus">Source on GitHub</a>
	<a class="launch-button" href="http://lab.hakim.se/fokus/">View Demo</a>
</div><footer><time datetime='2012-09-23'>2012-09-23</time><a class='footer-comment' href='/experiments/fokus'>13 comments</a></footer></article><article id='rvl-io' class='projects single'><aside class='actions'><a class='comment' href='/projects/rvl-io'>24</a></aside><h2>rvl.io</h2>
<a href="http://www.rvl.io/" class="image-link" title="Visit rvl.io">
	<img src="http://s3.amazonaws.com/hakim-static/portfolio/images/rvl-io.jpg" alt="rvl.io" width="320" height="305">
</a>
<p>
	As <a href="http://lab.hakim.se/reveal-js">reveal.js</a> has grown more popular there has been a lot of requests for an online editor and <a href="http://www.rvl.io/">rvl.io</a> is the answer. rvl.io is a service for authoring, storing and presenting slide decks without having to touch the underlying HTML of reveal.js. It was created by myself (frontend) and <a href="https://twitter.com/h__r__j">@h__r__j</a> (backend).
</p>

<div class="launch-dock">
	<a class="launch-button" href="http://www.rvl.io/">www.rvl.io</a>
